content:
A table component shows columns of data from a custom report in a dashboard. You can use color and scale to help users interpret the report data the table displays.

Required Editions: Salesforce Classic (not available in all orgs), Group (View Only), Professional, Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions.

User Permissions:
To create dashboards: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created: Run Reports AND Create and Customize Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you created in public folders: Edit My Dashboards
To edit and delete dashboards that you didnâ€™t create in public folders: Manage Dashboards in Public Folders
To create, edit, and delete dynamic dashboards: Manage Dynamic Dashboards

The default two-column table uses the first grouping and summary field from the chart in the source report. Customized tables allow null values in the results.

Setting	DESCRIPTION
Sort Rows By	Choose a sorting element.
Maximum Values Displayed	Set the maximum number of rows to include.
Show Chatter Photos	Display Chatter photos for up to 20 records in a table component.
Customize Table	Click this link to create a custom table.
Table Columns	Specify up to four columns to display in the table.
Sort Ascending	Sort the custom table in A-to-Z or smallest-to-largest order.
Sort Descending	Sort the custom table in Z-to-A or largest-to-smallest order.
Show Total	Display the total value for the chart.
Reset Table to Defaults	Go back to the default two-column table.
Low Range Color	Select a color to represent the low range, up to the first breakpoint.
Breakpoint 1	The value that separates the low and middle range colors on the dashboard.
Middle Range Color	Select a color to represent the middle range, between the first and second breakpoints.
Breakpoint 2	The value that separates the middle and high range colors on the dashboard. 
High Range Color	Select a color to represent the high range, beyond the second breakpoint.
title: Configuring Dashboard Table Components
